From a50ddc5ece80fc39dd71adacebff69462e7abf50 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dylan Van Assche <git@dylanvanassche.be>
Date: Mon, 9 Feb 2026 13:44:08 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] iio-sensor-proxy: register DBus objects after client
 hashtable init
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

`g_bus_own_name` has several callbacks which are invoked in a specific order [1],
`bus_acquired` callback is invoked before `name_acquired` callback.

iio-sensor-proxy creates hash tables per sensor to keep track of clients
in the `name_acquired` callback and exposes the DBus objects
in the `bus_acquired` callback.

This leads to a race condition when a DBus client is fast enough to register
and deregister at boot causing a crash as the client hash tables are not
created yet but the DBus objects are already exposed. If the client vanishes
too quickly, the hashtable is accessed which does not exist yet.

Move the DBus object registration to the `name_acquired` callback after
the hashtables are initialized to avoid this race condition.

[1] https://docs.gtk.org/gio/func.bus_own_name.html

